        <UserObject label="" mermaidData="{&#xa;  &quot;data&quot;: &quot;graph TD\n    %% Core components\n    CoreModule[Core Module: Cross-platform]\n    SourceLoader[Source Loader: URL, Buffer, File, Base64]\n    ParserSession[Parser Session: manages lifecycle]\n    TextExtractor[Text Extractor]\n    ImageExtractor[Image Extractor]\n    TableExtractor[Table Extractor]\n    ScreenshotExtractor[Screenshot Extractor]\n    InfoExtractor[Info Extractor]\n\n    %% Platform modules\n    NodeModule[Node Module: getHeader, Node utils]\n    BrowserModule[Browser Module: worker config]\n\n    %% Consumers\n    NodeConsumer[Node Consumer]\n    BrowserConsumer[Browser Consumer]\n\n    %% Connections\n    CoreModule --&gt; SourceLoader\n    CoreModule --&gt; ParserSession\n    ParserSession --&gt; TextExtractor\n    ParserSession --&gt; ImageExtractor\n    ParserSession --&gt; TableExtractor\n    ParserSession --&gt; ScreenshotExtractor\n    ParserSession --&gt; InfoExtractor\n\n    NodeModule --&gt; CoreModule\n    BrowserModule --&gt; CoreModule\n\n    NodeConsumer --&gt; CoreModule\n    NodeConsumer --&gt; NodeModule\n    BrowserConsumer --&gt; CoreModule\n    BrowserConsumer --&gt; BrowserModule\n\n    %% Notes (can be removed or kept as text nodes)\n    Note1[Note: Core Module contains all cross-platform logic]\n    Note2[Note: Node Module contains Node-only methods like getHeader]\n    Note3[Note: Browser Module configures PDF.js worker for browser]\n    Note4[Note: Extractors are modular and reusable]\n    Note5[Note: Parser Session provides extractors and lifecycle]\n    Note6[Note: Source Loader abstracts input types]\n\n    Note1 --- CoreModule\n    Note2 --- NodeModule\n    Note3 --- BrowserModule\n    Note4 --- TextExtractor\n    Note5 --- ParserSession\n    Note6 --- SourceLoader\n&quot;&#xa;}" id="HXTLwd__SZcSvWQXaKgc-1">
